==English==

===Etymology===
French ''abstinent'', Latin ''abstinens'', present participle of ''abstinere''. See [[Abstain]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-abstinent.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''abstinent'''

#[[Refraining]] from [[indulgence]], especially from the indulgence of appetite; [[abstemious]]; [[continent]]; [[temperate]]. - [[Beaumont and Fletcher]]
===Noun===
'''abstinent'''

#One who [[abstains]].
#''[[Ecclesiastical History]]:'' One of a sect who appeared in France and Spain in the 3d century.
